using 'official' Qt install
note: Qt5.7 doesn't seem to have proper pkg-config files... so I hacked my own up
The Qt 'official' frameworks use relative, @rpath paths.
The homebrew Qt libs don't.

  export PKG_CONFIG_PATH=/Users/ben/crap/pkgconfig
  export PATH=$PATH:/Users/ben/Qt5.7.0/5.7/clang_64/bin

need to set the rpath in the exe so it'll find the frameworks when bundled:
  go build -ldflags="-extldflags '-rpath @executable_path/../Frameworks'"


